ZH: 今天早上我的闹钟没有响。
EN: My alarm didn't go off this morning.

ZH: 我的闹钟是一只可爱的熊猫。
EN: My alarm clock is a cute panda.

ZH: 请设定你的闹钟，明天早上要早起。
EN: Please set your alarm clock, you need to wake up early tomorrow morning.

ZH: 我喜欢用音乐作为我的闹钟铃声。
EN: I like to use music as my alarm clock ringtone.

ZH: 我弄丢了我的闹钟，现在每天都迟到。
EN: I lost my alarm clock, now I am late every day.

ZH: 我的闹钟是一个拟真的火箭。
EN: My alarm clock is a realistic rocket.

ZH: 忘记设定闹钟是我早起的最大障碍。
EN: Forgetting to set the alarm clock is my biggest obstacle to waking up early.

ZH: 每天闹钟响了后我都立刻起床，不会再睡。
EN: I get up right after my alarm clock goes off every day, I won't sleep again.

ZH: 他的闹钟铃声是一段海浪声。
EN: His alarm clock ringtone is a sound of waves.

ZH: 请告诉我你的闹钟时间，我帮你叫醒。
EN: Please tell me your alarm clock time, I will help you wake up.

ZH: 你的闹钟响了几次以后才能起床？
EN: How many times does your alarm clock go off before you get up?

ZH: 他的闹钟带有夜灯功能。
EN: His alarm clock has a night light function.

ZH: 有人愿意用数码闹钟来代替传统的闹钟。
EN: Some people are willing to use a digital alarm clock instead of a traditional one.

ZH: 请把你的闹钟设定在六点，我们要早起。
EN: Please set your alarm clock for six o'clock, we need to wake up early.

ZH: 他的闹钟是一个带闹铃的鸡。
EN: His alarm clock is a rooster with an alarm.

ZH: 我的闹钟是一只飞行的小鸟。
EN: My alarm clock is a flying bird.

ZH: 有人宁愿不设定闹钟也不早起床。
EN: Some people would rather not set an alarm clock than wake up early.

ZH: 请确保你的闹钟声音足够大，以便早起。
EN: Please make sure your alarm clock sound is loud enough to wake up early.

ZH: 你的闹钟不会停止响了吧？
EN: Your alarm clock won't stop ringing, right?

ZH: 我喜欢用数字闹钟而不是传统的机械闹钟。
EN: I prefer to use digital alarm clocks rather than traditional mechanical ones.
